Hand-forged damascus created from multiple alloys of stainless steel.  This beautiful material is heat treated to Rockwell 58-59 for excellent sharpness and edge retention.  As with any high performance blade, clean and dry after use.



Frame:  Koftgari - 24K Gold

Koftgari is a technique of hand-inlaying 24K gold into a tool steel frame.  The gold is burnished into a fine grid scribed into the steel, and the frame is "parkerized" to a deep brown/blue background.  The tool steel frame has no stainless properties and care should be taken to protect it.  Avoid exposure to wet, acidic or salt environments.



Scale/Inlay:  Ironwood

Our range of woods rank among the rarest and most spectacular in the world - hand selected for premium figure, color, and durability.  Where applicable, we stabilize the wood with acrylic resin, to provide additional protection.  Wood is a natural material and can shift, expand or contract over time.



Gemstone:  Citrine

Fittings:

title: For Sale:  Lone Wolf Paul Pocket Leopard Stone Damascus LM21920 brand new in the box
location: dix hills, Long Island, New York
postcontent:
his knife with exotic genuine Leopard Skin Jasper Stone Agate handles and Damascus blade will be a beautiful addition to your collection or your pocket. The stone is hand cut, shaped, polished and fit to each knife. The pattern in the leopard stone is varied and with its spotted appearance it is easy to see how it got its name.

The blade is forged stainless Damascus steel that is heat treated, tempered, cryogenically frozen, polished and then etched twice with a special process to bring out the beautiful pattern in the steel. This unique steel combines the ancient art of Damascus forging with modern stainless steels to produce “art in steel” that complements the natural stone making a truly gorgeous knife. Gold plated fasteners and lock components complement the handle and blade on this fine knife.

The patented Paul® lock system locks the blade both open and closed and is extremely safe, strong and easy to use. Paul® Knives are famous for their precise fit and function and have been a favorite of knife enthusiasts throughout the world for many years. The patented axial mechanism also provides easy one-handed-opening of the knife. Simply grip the button between your thumb and forefinger and squeeze, the handle is then released to rotate freely away from the blade into the open and locked position. Reversing this procedure will close and lock the blade. Paul® knives are simple to use, elegant in design, extremely strong and safe.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Magnum Research Desert Eagle .44 Magnum
postcontent:
What’s that? You’re looking for the “Desert Eagle”. Well, I just so happen to have one that I possibly could part with.

I came across this wonderful relic of Jewish technology while on the quest for the “Ark of the Covenant” with Professor Jones. You know that crazy whip wielding archeologist. 

It was lying in a dusty glass box with “Nazi Skinner Mark VII” written above it. As I slowly opened the box, I heard trumpets sound in the distant sky and shimmer of satiny silver came from the box. As I reached for the hand cannon, like Mjolnir to Thor, this Desert Eagle flew to my hand. I knew at that time that I was meant to wield this formidable weapon.

(This could possibly be an embellishment of the facts.)

That was nearly 15 years ago. Since then I have acquired 2 more of these beasts. I have an original Mark I and another Mark VII with multiple caliber and barrel lengths. I don’t have a real need to get rid of this “Hammer of Israel” but I need to make room and am thinning out the herd. 

This is not a .50 AE; I was never one for that caliber, so I never purchased one. But this is however one of the original ones marked “Made in Israel”, and is in the caliber .44 Magnum. 

And in my opinion the most fun to shoot. My favorite has always been the proper .44 Magnum Desert Eagle. 

When you have one of these guns, one of your favorite things about owning it is this. The face of people who hold it, and if they are lucky, get to shoot it for the first time. 

This gun makes peckers hard and kittens wet. Pulling the trigger either makes you smile or makes you cry. Just tell people it is twice as powerful as a 22, that’s why they call it a 44. 

Stand back and prepare to upload to youtube. 
This gun is an absolute joy to shoot. 

Let me know if you have anything interesting to trade. 

Thank you for your consideration. 

Update - For those that are interested. This gun has been traded recently. Consider this to be a warning of individuals out there. The gun I traded this for was a 629-1 and a 45-70 rifle. 

The problem was that the individual Daniel R. Rivers at REDACTED or REDACTED completely misrepresented the 629-1. Upon closer inspection when I got home and after I disassembled the gun. It became evident that some of the internals on this gun had been glued together to replicate proper function. I attempted to contact Mr. Rivers in an attempt to make this right and he refused to respond to my emails, texts or phone calls.
